1 released on parole.
2 (5) Mandatory reentry supervision is not a commutation of sentence or any other form
3 of clemency.
4 (6) A[No] hearing shall not be required for the board to order an inmate to mandatory
5 reentry supervision pursuant to subsection (1) of this section. Terms of supervision
6 for inmates released on mandatory reentry supervision shall be established as
7 follows:
8 (a) 1. The board shall promulgate[adopt] administrative regulations in
9 accordance with KRS Chapter 13A establishing general conditions
10 applicable to each inmate ordered to mandatory reentry supervision
11 pursuant to subsection (1) of this section.
12 2. If an inmate is ordered to mandatory reentry supervision, the board's
13 order shall:
14 a. Set forth the general conditions; and[ shall]
15 b. Require the inmate to comply with the general conditions and any
16 requirements imposed by the department in accordance with this
17 section;
18 (b) Upon intake of an inmate ordered to mandatory reentry supervision by the
19 board, the department shall use the results of the risk and needs assessment
20 administered pursuant to KRS 439.3104(1) to establish appropriate terms and
21 conditions of supervision, taking into consideration the level of risk to public
22 safety, criminal risk factors, and the need for treatment and other
23 interventions. The terms and conditions imposed by the department under this
24 paragraph shall not conflict with the general conditions adopted by the board
25 pursuant to paragraph (a) of this subsection; and
26 (c) The powers and duties assigned to the commissioner in relation to probation
27 or parole under KRS 439.470 shall be assigned to the commissioner in
